	<h1>Page Links (1)</h1>

	This page is called <em>examples/navigation/PageLinks1</em>, and it is about the <strong>PageLink</strong> component.<br/><br/>
	
	All the examples so far have included a PageLink.  
	What happens when you click on the link? It sends a render request.<br/>
	A <strong>render request</strong> asks Tapestry to get an instance of a page, activate it, render the output and return it.<br/><br/>
  	
	Here's an example of some tml code using a PageLink:<br/>
	<code>&lt;a t:type="pagelink" t:page="examples/navigation/PageLinks2" href="#"&gt;To PageLinks2&lt;/a&gt;</code><br/><br/>
	
	Here's the code in action:<br/> 
	<a t:type="pagelink" t:page="examples/navigation/PageLinks2" href="#">To PageLinks2</a><br/><br/>
	
	It generates a link whose URL looks like this:<br/>
	<code>http://myhost/jumpstart/examples/navigation/pagelinks2</code><br/><br/>

